================================================================
What's queued next (per SIMD plan summary table)
================================================================

Per the cvvdp-cpu SIMD optimization plan:

- **Chunk 5** (SIMD CSF apply + persistent rayon pool) — running
  concurrently in a sibling workspace.
- After all 5 chunks land, projected 1024² post-SIMD wall is in
  the 50-80 ms range — within reach of the 50 ms Phase-1 target.
- **Phase-2 structural** (strip pipeline, band fusion) — multi-week
  effort to close the remaining gap with zensim (14.66 ms target).
  Out of scope for the SIMD chain.

DO NOT (binding for future agents):

1. DO NOT cite "FMA precision" for any byte/JOD drift from this chunk
   (per W44-66 user correction). The SIMD wins come from the
   compute-bound 13-tap kernel pattern; the 1e-5 parity floor is
   well below the 1e-4 JOD floor.
2. DO NOT widen the 1e-4 JOD parity gate based on this work.
3. DO NOT remove the SIMD blur module — Phase-2 structural work
   (strip pipeline) benefits.
4. DO NOT default-enable `avx512` on cvvdp-cpu until `simd_math`
   gains v4 / v4x variants (Chunk 3's outstanding bug, not this
   chunk's).
5. DO NOT respawn this chunk expecting MORE perf — the speedup is
   already 1.7-2× across all sizes, well above the gate. The next
   structural lever is strip-pipeline, not "more aggressive SIMD here".
